          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Angular distribution of 1000 fission fragments was",
                "analyzed.  The anisotropy ratio, n(theta)/n(90deg),",
                "is to be represented as,",
                " r= n(theta)/n(90deg) = a + b*(cos(theta))**2,  where",
                "    a=(0.31+-0.037), and b=(0.99+-0.24).",
                "Angle(theta) is the angle between fragment direction",
                "and incident beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MISC-COL": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MISC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " cos(theta)**2 which is given in Fig.3 of Nucl.",
                "Sci.Appl.9B(1976)17."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The width of gaussian 'K' distribution, K(0)**2, was",
